	   <tr><td colspan=2>Footman's lances have always been, and always shall be two-handed weapons. Having used one in real life I can attest to their sheer size, being over 9 feet long with a small shield front at the lance base. Even if you could find a lance that weighs under 10 pounds ( maybe titanium and driftwood ), you would still need both hands because it would be completely unwieldy with one hand. To answer the gripe about using a shield with a lance, having also done jousting with the SCA and not being small ( 6 - 1 at 265 lbs ) I can attest that using even a 16 foot jousting lance with no metal bindings is a task, as all your strength is used just to aim the beast, the weight being rested against the shoulder and side-body, the force of the blow being delivered by the horse. It would be ludicrous for Verant to make this a one handed item and they know it, at least they got something right.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
